article.headline: Pennsylvania 91, Columbia 76
article.story: NEW YORK (AP) -- Ibrahim Jaaber came off the bench to spark a first-half run that helped Pennsylvania defeat Columbia 91-76 Friday night. With Penn (11-8, 4-2 Ivy League) trailing 26-22 with 7:49 left in the half, Jaaber converted a steal into a layup to start a 14-4 run that gave the Quakers a 36-30 lead. Penn expanded its lead to 45-36 at halftime as Jaaber scoring eight of his career-best 16 points. Columbia (5-14, 2-5) made a brief run early in the second half, cutting the edge to 49-44, but Tim Begley hit a 3-point shot to trigger an 8-2 run that gave the Quakers an insurmountable lead. Penn's lead reached 18 -- 67-49 -- with 11:25 remaining and the Lions never got closer than nine. Jeff Schniffer led the Quakers, who have won four in a row, with a career-high 28 points, 17 in the first half. Mark Zoller scored 15 points, Tim Begley had 13 and Adam Chubb 11 for Penn. Matt Preston led the Lions with 28 points and Dragutin Kravic added 20.
